# Unified App — Code Rules

See also: `date-time-pickers.mdc` (picker UX) and `ui-theme.mdc` (theme tokens & UI consistency).

- All components are functional (no class components)
- All API calls go through RTK Query — never raw fetch in components
- All forms use React Hook Form + Zod validation
- All lists use FlatList with keyExtractor and memoized renderItem
- Use React.memo on all list item components
- Never use inline styles — use StyleSheet.create or Nativewind classes
- Supabase calls always go through RTK Query baseQuery, not directly
- Every screen must handle: loading state, error state, empty state
- Use expo-secure-store for JWT, AsyncStorage for non-sensitive data

## What NOT to do

- Never use class components
- Never use `any` type
- Never put API calls directly in components (always RTK Query)
- Never use inline StyleSheet objects (define outside component)
- Never use index as FlatList keyExtractor
- Never hardcode colors — use theme/colors.ts tokens
